2. The first heart transplant in the world took place in 1967. It was performed by 
Dr Christiaan Barnard at Groote Schuur Hospital in Cape Town.
3. There are more than 2000 shipwrecks in and around the South Africa coast.
4. Guess who is the second largest fruit producer in the world? Yes, you guessed it, South Africa.
5. South Africa is the only country in the entire world where a street has produced two Nobel Prize 
